                    <msContents>
                        <summary>An official letter from Flavius Marianos, possibly the governor of Palaestina Tertia, to Theodoros, son of Obodianos. Also meager fragments of other papyri, but nothing can be said of their contents nor of their relationship to the letter.</summary>
                        <msItemStruct>
                            <note type="general">Letter proper written in a wide column (55 cm) along the ﬁbers.  The first line was written in a large, ﬂamboyant, upright hand with occasional very small letters. The hand of the second line is similar but perhaps not the same, and the letters are much smaller. The contents of the letter was written by the same hand as that of the second line, with letters of a height in between those of the two ﬁrst lines. Text of some fragments is written transversa charta, probably on separate sheets (possibly two), and wrapped around the main document.</note>
                            <note type="general">Reproduced in plates LXXXII-LXXXIII</note>
                            <note type="local_note">Field no. XIII</note>
